a.org/resource/Peres_Jepchirchir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peres_Jepchirchir\"}, {\"begin\": 274, \"end\": 279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997176019, \"rank\": 2.8245601689788894e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one almighty different reception\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 324}, {\"ngram\": \"her medal ceremony\", \"from\": 328, \"to\": 346}, {\"ngram\": \"the Covid-hit Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 359, \"to\": 384}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because for the first time ever the tradition of handing the men's marathon winner his gold medal at the closing ceremony will be swapped out, making way for the women's marathon to take the glory on the final night of sporting festivities.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 423}, {\"ngram\": \"the tradition\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 442}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's marathon winner\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 479}, {\"ngram\": \"his gold medal\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 494}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"way\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's marathon\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"the glory\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"the final night\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting festivities\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 636}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is just one of the changes that organisers hope will make Paris 2024, which marks 100 days to go today, the most equal Olympics yet.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 700, \"end\": 710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4557414886538438e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the changes\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 668}, {\"ngram\": \"organisers\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 684}, {\"ngram\": \"100 days\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 732}, {\"ngram\": \"the most equal Olympics\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the Games were last in the French capital, in 1924, women made up 4.4 per cent of the athletes, and there were only 175 participants across 10 disciplines - including swimming, fencing and table tennis, but not athletics.\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.988139910637912, \"rank\": 0.011077786358949017, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 790}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 838}, {\"ngram\": \"4.4 per cent\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 875}, {\"ngram\": \"only 175 participants\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 913}, {\"ngram\": \"10 disciplines\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 935}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"fencing\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"table\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 975}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"not athletics\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1001}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now at the 33rd Olympiad there will be a total of 10,500 athletes - over 50 per cent of whom will be women.\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1111, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 33rd Olympiad\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"a total\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"10,500 athletes\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1069}, {\"ngram\": \"over 50 per cent\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over 85 per cent of the 32 sports will have full gender equality, with the true numbers showing there will be 152 women's events and 157 men's events.\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1262, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"85 per cent\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1128}, {\"ngram\": \"the 32 sports\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1145}, {\"ngram\": \"full gender equality\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"the true numbers\", \"from\": 1183, \"to\": 1199}, {\"ngram\": \"152 women's events\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1240}, {\"ngram\": \"157 men's events\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1261}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City AM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the game\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1280}, {\"ngram\": \"The Turnover\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1298}, {\"ngram\": \"your weekly roundup\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1319}, {\"ngram\": \"sport business news\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"City AM's sports desk\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1416}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Changes have been made to achieve parity not just by increasing the number of women in each event, though.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1525, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Changes\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"parity\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1459}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"each event\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Men are now able to compete in synchronised swimming, known as artistic swimming, although it is impossible to achieve parity in other events such as women's heptathlon and men's decathlon.\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1715, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Men\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1529}, {\"ngram\": \"synchronised swimming\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"artistic swimming\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1606}, {\"ngram\": \"parity\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1651}, {\"ngram\": \"other events\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"women's heptathlon\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1694}, {\"ngram\": \"men's decathlon\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We were very happy that this year in particular, when we celebrate that we are going back to Paris after 100 years, that this is going to be the first time the Olympics are going to have 50:50 parity,\\\" Nicole Hoevertsz, International Olympic Committee vice-president, tellsCity A.M. \\\"That required a lot of work from the side of the International Federations.\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 2078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997176019, \"rank\": 2.8245601689788894e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1938, \"end\": 1969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_governing_body\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Federations\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_governing_body\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_governing_body\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"100 years\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"50:50 parity\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"vice\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2021}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2029}, {\"ngram\": \"the side\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The poorer places that were allocated [help], were actually allocated to mostly women and women's events.\\\"\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2185, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The poorer places\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2096}, {\"ngram\": \"mostly women\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2164}, {\"ngram\": \"women's events\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But true 50:50 is elusive, adds Aruban former synchronised swimmer Hoevertsz.\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Aruban former synchronised swimmer Hoevertsz\", \"from\": 2219, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think that is really possible,\\\" she adds.\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2317, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are some sports like synchronised swimming where you are going to see the reverse, where it used to be a sport that was only open for women.\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2465, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some sports\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2340}, {\"ngram\": \"synchronised swimming\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"the reverse\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2406}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now in Paris, it's going to be open for the first time for men for the mixed and the team.\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997176019, \"rank\": 2.8245601689788894e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2520}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2528}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2555}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So you get to see different sports, depending on the actual events and the actual programme.\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2651, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"different sports\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"the actual events\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2625}, {\"ngram\": \"the actual programme\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2650}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe it's not 100 per cent possible to have a 50:50 but I think we have come a long way.\\\"\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2742, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cent\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2679}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there remains to be concerns over the full run to gender parity with some former Olympians questioning where transgender athletes - male to female - fit into the Games from a fairness perspective.\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2944, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2776}, {\"ngram\": \"the full run\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2794}, {\"ngram\": \"gender parity\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"some former Olympians\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2838}, {\"ngram\": \"where transgender athletes - male\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"female - fit\", \"from\": 2888, \"to\": 2900}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 2915}, {\"ngram\": \"a fairness perspective\", \"from\": 2921, \"to\": 2943}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The current IOC line states that individual federations will decide on their transgender policy, with Hoevertsz saying \\\"no if it complies with what we agreed to\\\" when pressed on whether the Olympic body would try to stand in the way of any federation policy.\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"individual federations\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 3001}, {\"ngram\": \"their transgender policy\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3041}, {\"ngram\": \"Hoevertsz\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3057}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic body\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3148}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 3171, \"to\": 3178}, {\"ngram\": \"any federation policy\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Critics say policies such as the preference for at least one male and one female athlete in each nation's delegation, and the need for both a male and female flag bearer, are unnecessary and tokenistic.\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Critics\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3213}, {\"ngram\": \"policies\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3226}, {\"ngram\": \"the preference\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3249}, {\"ngram\": \"at least one male\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3271}, {\"ngram\": \"one female athlete\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3294}, {\"ngram\": \"each nation's delegation\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3322}, {\"ngram\": \"the need\", \"from\": 3328, \"to\": 3336}, {\"ngram\": \"both a male and female flag bearer\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3375}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One former Olympic coach mused toCity A.M.whether, theoretically, a micronation would be disciplined because they only took one female athlete.\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3552, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One former Olympic coach\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3433}, {\"ngram\": \"toCity\", \"from\": 3440, \"to\": 3446}, {\"ngram\": \"a micronation\", \"from\": 3475, \"to\": 3488}, {\"ngram\": \"one female athlete\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3551}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It appears choppy waters remain in the details of what will be dubbed the gender parity Olympics, and those formerly and currently in the sport still have questions over parts of the journey to 50:50.\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"choppy waters\", \"from\": 3565, \"to\": 3578}, {\"ngram\": \"the details\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3600}, {\"ngram\": \"the gender parity Olympics\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3650}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 3688, \"to\": 3697}, {\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 3709, \"to\": 3718}, {\"ngram\": \"parts\", \"from\": 3724, \"to\": 3729}, {\"ngram\": \"the journey\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in 2024, 100 years on from the last Paris Games, there is a stark shift towards true equality at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3756, \"to\": 3870, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last Paris Games\", \"from\": 3787, \"to\": 3807}, {\"ngram\": \"a stark shift\", \"from\": 3818, \"to\": 3831}, {\"ngram\": \"true equality\", \"from\": 3840, \"to\": 3853}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3857, \"to\": 3869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And when those 10,000-plus athletes descend on the French capital for two weeks of elite, over half of whom are women, there will be an important moment in the countless chronicles of sporting history.\", \"from\": 3871, \"to\": 4072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3922, \"end\": 3928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.988139910637912, \"rank\": 0.011077786358949017, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those 10,000-plus athletes\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3906}, {\"ngram\": \"two weeks\", \"from\": 3941, \"to\": 3950}, {\"ngram\": \"elite\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 3959}, {\"ngram\": \"half\", \"from\": 3966, \"to\": 3970}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 3988}, {\"ngram\": \"an important moment\", \"from\": 4004, \"to\": 4023}, {\"ngram\": \"the countless chronicles\", \"from\": 4027, \"to\": 4051}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting history\", \"from\": 4055, \"to\": 4071}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because a 50:50 games is a triumph, and something fans should celebrate across this sporting summer.\", \"from\": 4074, \"to\": 4174, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 50:50 games\", \"from\": 4082, \"to\": 4095}, {\"ngram\": \"a triumph\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4108}, {\"ngram\": \"something fans\", \"from\": 4114, \"to\": 4128}, {\"ngram\": \"this sporting summer\", \"from\": 4153, \"to\": 4173}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Share this article Subscribe to the City AM newsletter to have our top stories delivered directly to your inbox.\", \"from\": 4176, \"to\": 4289, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this article\", \"from\": 4182, \"to\": 4194}, {\"ngram\": \"the City AM newsletter\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4230}, {\"ngram\": \"our top stories\", \"from\": 4239, \"to\": 4254}, {\"ngram\": \"your inbox\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow us for breaking news and latest updates\", \"from\": 4291, \"to\": 4337, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4300}, {\"ngram\": \"news\", \"from\": 4314, \"to\": 4318}, {\"ngram\": \"latest updates\", \"from\": 4323, \"to\": 4337}]}]}"